definition.value: A third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic bearing pyridinium-1-ylmethyl and {[(2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-{[(2-carboxypropan-2-yl)oxy]imino}acetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

A hydrate that is the pentahydrate of ceftazidime, a cephalosporin having 7beta-[(2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-{[(2-carboxypropan-2-yl)oxy]imino}acetyl]amino and 3-pyridinium-1-ylmethyl side-groups.
An alkylbenzene that is benzene substituted by a butan-2-yl group.

A third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with a [(2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-4-carboxybut-2-enoyl]amino substituent at the 7 position of the cephem skeleton. An orally-administered agent, ceftibuten is used as the dihydrate to treat urinary-tract and respiratory-tract infections.
Saturated acyclic nitrogen hydrides having the general formula NnHn+2.
A manganese oxoanion that consists of manganic acid where one of the two OH groups has been deprotonated.
A manganese oxoanion that consists of hypomanganic acid where one of the three OH groups has been deprotonated.
A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of two protons from hypomanganic acid.
